# Cloudflare D1

D1 is serverless SQLite at the edge. Full SQL support, automatic replication, and direct integration with Workers.

## Setup

### Create a Database

```bash
# Create a D1 database
wrangler d1 create my-database
# Output:
# Created database 'my-database'
# database_id = "xxxx-yyyy-zzzz"

# List databases
wrangler d1 list
```

### wrangler.toml

```toml
[[d1_databases]]
binding = "DB"
database_name = "my-database"
database_id = "xxxx-yyyy-zzzz"
```

## Migrations

D1 uses file-based migrations in the `migrations/` directory.

```bash
# Create a migration
wrangler d1 migrations create my-database create_users_table
# Creates: migrations/0001_create_users_table.sql
```

```sql
-- migrations/0001_create_users_table.sql
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS users (
  id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,
  email TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,
  name TEXT NOT NULL,
  role TEXT DEFAULT 'user',
  created_at TEXT DEFAULT (datetime('now')),
  updated_at TEXT DEFAULT (datetime('now'))
);

CREATE INDEX idx_users_email ON users(email);
CREATE INDEX idx_users_role ON users(role);
```

```bash
# Apply migrations (local)
wrangler d1 migrations apply my-database --local

# Apply migrations (remote/production)
wrangler d1 migrations apply my-database --remote

# List migration status
wrangler d1 migrations list my-database --remote
```

## Worker API

```typescript
export interface Env {
  DB: D1Database;
}

export default {
  async fetch(request: Request, env: Env): Promise<Response> {
    const url = new URL(request.url);

    // SELECT — query rows
    if (url.pathname === '/users') {
      const { results } = await env.DB.prepare(
        'SELECT id, email, name, role FROM users WHERE role = ? ORDER BY created_at DESC LIMIT ?'
      ).bind('admin', 50).all();
      return Response.json(results);
    }

    // SELECT — single row
    if (url.pathname.startsWith('/users/')) {
      const id = url.pathname.split('/')[2];
      const user = await env.DB.prepare(
        'SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = ?'
      ).bind(id).first();
      if (!user) return new Response('Not Found', { status: 404 });
      return Response.json(user);
    }

    // INSERT
    if (request.method === 'POST' && url.pathname === '/users') {
      const { email, name, role } = await request.json() as any;
      const result = await env.DB.prepare(
        'INSERT INTO users (email, name, role) VALUES (?, ?, ?) RETURNING id'
      ).bind(email, name, role || 'user').first();
      return Response.json(result, { status: 201 });
    }

    // UPDATE
    if (request.method === 'PUT' && url.pathname.startsWith('/users/')) {
      const id = url.pathname.split('/')[2];
      const { name, role } = await request.json() as any;
      await env.DB.prepare(
        'UPDATE users SET name = ?, role = ?, updated_at = datetime("now") WHERE id = ?'
      ).bind(name, role, id).run();
      return new Response('Updated', { status: 200 });
    }

    // DELETE
    if (request.method === 'DELETE' && url.pathname.startsWith('/users/')) {
      const id = url.pathname.split('/')[2];
      await env.DB.prepare('DELETE FROM users WHERE id = ?').bind(id).run();
      return new Response('Deleted', { status: 200 });
    }

    // BATCH — multiple statements in a transaction
    if (request.method === 'POST' && url.pathname === '/batch') {
      const results = await env.DB.batch([
        env.DB.prepare('INSERT INTO users (email, name) VALUES (?, ?)').bind('a@b.com', 'Alice'),
        env.DB.prepare('INSERT INTO users (email, name) VALUES (?, ?)').bind('c@d.com', 'Bob'),
      ]);
      return Response.json({ inserted: results.length });
    }

    return new Response('Not Found', { status: 404 });
  },
};
```

## CLI Queries

```bash
# Execute SQL directly
wrangler d1 execute my-database --remote --command "SELECT * FROM users LIMIT 10"

# Execute SQL from file
wrangler d1 execute my-database --remote --file ./seed.sql

# Local execution (uses local SQLite)
wrangler d1 execute my-database --local --command "SELECT count(*) FROM users"
```

## D1 API Methods

```typescript
// prepare(sql) — create a prepared statement
const stmt = env.DB.prepare('SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = ?');

// bind(...values) — bind parameters (positional)
const bound = stmt.bind(42);

// all() — return all rows
const { results, meta } = await bound.all();
// results: array of row objects
// meta: { duration, rows_read, rows_written, last_row_id, changes }

// first(column?) — return first row or column value
const row = await stmt.bind(42).first();        // { id, email, name, ... }
const email = await stmt.bind(42).first('email'); // string

// run() — execute statement without returning rows (INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE)
const { meta } = await env.DB.prepare('DELETE FROM users WHERE id = ?').bind(42).run();

// raw() — return rows as arrays instead of objects
const rows = await stmt.bind(42).raw();  // [[1, 'alice@...', 'Alice']]

// batch() — execute multiple statements in a transaction
const results = await env.DB.batch([stmt1, stmt2, stmt3]);
```

## SQLite Features Supported

- ACID transactions via `batch()`
- JSON functions: `json_extract()`, `json_array()`, `json_object()`
- Full-text search: `fts5`
- Window functions: `ROW_NUMBER()`, `RANK()`, `LAG()`, `LEAD()`
- CTEs (WITH clauses)
- RETURNING clause for INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE
- Generated columns
- Partial indexes
